msgid ""
msgstr ""
"Project-Id-Version: Yakuza 6 Translation\n"
"Last-Translator: SavT\n"
"MIME-Version: 1.0\n"
"Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8\n"
"Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit\n"
"Language: it\n"

msgctxt "0||||4"
msgid "Now then, we were just gettin' to\r\nhow I can be sure Yuta is the father."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1||||4"
msgid "It all has to do with when Masuzoe and\r\nTatsukawa first noticed Haruka's pregnancy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2||||4"
msgid "Truth is, they've been keeping an eye\r\non Yuta since he was a little boy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3||||4"
msgid "You watched Yuta?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4||||4"
msgid "Wh-Why is that?\r\nWhy were the two of them watching me!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5||||4"
msgid "Because, you are the heir\r\nto the Saio Triad."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6||||4"
msgid "Huh?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7||||4"
msgid "What?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8||||4"
msgid "Yuta Usami. You are the biological son\r\nof the Saio Triad ringleader, Big Lo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "10||||4"
msgid "Wh-What are you talking about?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11||||4"
msgid "But according to Lo, his son Jimmy was\r\nmurdered in Kamurocho three months ago."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12||||4"
msgid "Care to explain, Masuzoe!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13||||4"
msgid "Jimmy was a legitimate son of his, yes.\r\nYuta is simply his younger brother."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14||||4"
msgid "And upon Jimmy's death in Kamurocho,\r\nthe Saio Triad passes to the next of kin."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15||||4"
msgid "Put it in terms Kiryu-san's gonna\r\nunderstand, Masuzoe."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16||||4"
msgid "The Saio Triad has survived through the\r\nbrutal conflict in mainland China for ages."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17||||4"
msgid "That said, we've consistently been plagued by\r\nbetrayal from subordinates who desire power."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18||||4"
msgid "To put a stop to that, the Saio leadership\r\nput their faith in the power of their blood."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19||||4"
msgid "Their blood? Like a lineage?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20||||4"
msgid "Exactly. The boss makes officers of his\r\nfamily, and that keeps him safe."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21||||4"
msgid "Take Ed. He's the boss's cousin."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22||||4"
msgid "But the golden rule is that only the\r\nboss's biological son can inherit the triad."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23||||4"
msgid "Can you imagine if the boss were\r\nto have more than one son, though?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24||||4"
msgid "A war of succession."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26||||4"
msgid "Each heir would form their own separate\r\nfaction and tear the triad apart from within."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27||||4"
msgid "To avoid that, past Saio bosses have\r\nopted to exile any sons past the first."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28||||4"
msgid "These estranged sons act as an insurance\r\npolicy, if something should befall the first."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29||||4"
msgid "So yer sayin' Yuta's\r\nthe insurance here?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30||||4"
msgid "Now hold on a sec.\r\nDoes that mean he's Chinese?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31||||4"
msgid "There's no way. You can't expect me\r\nto believe something like that!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32||||4"
msgid "I suppose that's your call to make."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33||||4"
msgid "But you never knew your parents, did you?\r\nAnd remember your childhood in the orphanage?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35||||4"
msgid "Since you were a baby, Tatsukawa and I\r\nhave been protecting you from the shadows."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "36||||4"
msgid "We had to make sure you never knew the truth.\r\nMake sure you didn't get yourself killed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37||||4"
msgid "Those were our orders direct\r\nfrom the Saio Triad leadership."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38||||4"
msgid "We were nothing more than discarded\r\n<font_kind=yakuza_italic>heihaizi</font_kind> when the Saio Triad took us in."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39||||4"
msgid "What choice did we have but\r\nto accept their way of life!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "40||||4"
msgid "And that's why Tatsukawa\r\nbecame my friend?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41||||4"
msgid "Was none of it real?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42||||4"
msgid "Do you remember why you asked\r\nhim to teach you Chinese?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43||||4"
msgid "I'm the one who arranged that cute girl\r\nto come here and motivate you to study."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44||||4"
msgid "All so you'd be ready on the\r\noff chance you actually became the heir."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46||||4"
msgid "Tatsukawa allowed us to monitor you\r\nclosely without you even realizing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "47||||4"
msgid "How recently were you doing this?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48||||4"
msgid "All through your little tryst with Haruka.\r\nWe were aware of every last detail."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50||||4"
msgid "That's how we came to know she\r\nwas pregnant before anyone else."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51||||4"
msgid "But being the fool you are, you continued\r\non with your life like nothing ever happened."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52||||4"
msgid "And that's why you and Tatsukawa tried to\r\nconvince Haruka to abort him, right?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53||||4"
msgid "Huh!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55||||4"
msgid "I get it now. That must've been the call\r\nKiyomi-san overheard in her bar!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56||||4"
msgid "The one where Tatsukawa was sayin'\r\nt'get rid o' the baby!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57||||4"
msgid "We could never allow the family lineage\r\nto be sullied by inferior Japanese blood."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58||||4"
msgid "And worse still, it'd be disastrous for our\r\nbackup heir to go around pumping out kids."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59||||4"
msgid "It was our job to pluck out\r\nthose weeds before they grew."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "60||||4"
msgid "Y'can't talk about kids like that, asshole!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61||||4"
msgid "But before we could do that, Haruka\r\ndisappeared from town without a trace."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62||||4"
msgid "And go figure, this guy here was the one\r\nwho made sure she did. Right, Hirose-san?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64||||4"
msgid "I was out wanderin' through town\r\none day when she came up to me."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65||||4"
msgid "It looked like she'd seen a ghost."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "66||||4"
msgid "Makes sense, though. She'd just found out\r\nher beau was heir to the Saio Triad."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "67||||4"
msgid "That, and his keepers were telling\r\nher to get rid of her baby."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68||||4"
msgid "Be a shock to anyone, wouldn't it?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69||||4"
msgid "Took her a'while to calm down\r\nand tell me the whole story."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70||||4"
msgid "Well, I was as bored\r\nthen as I am now."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71||||4"
msgid "But she wasn't about to let 'em\r\nkill the life inside her."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72||||4"
msgid "'Specially not just to satisfy some\r\nfaceless gang of Chinese thugs."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73||||4"
msgid "Haruka wanted to give her boy the\r\nrespect he deserved. She was firm on that."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75||||4"
msgid "Even before Haruto was born, his mother\r\ncared about him more than anything else."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76||||4"
msgid "And in order to help her son, she needed\r\nsomewhere safe. That's where I came in."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77||||4"
msgid "It's his fault that we lost track\r\nof Haruka after she skipped town."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "78||||4"
msgid "However, we still had time before\r\nwe had to report it up to the boss."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79||||4"
msgid "After all, at the time, Yuta Usami\r\nwas just an insurance policy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "80||||4"
msgid "If Tatsukawa and I kept our mouths shut,\r\nnot even Yuta would be the wiser."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81||||4"
msgid "We should have been able to live our\r\nlives like nothing had ever happened."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82||||4"
msgid "Even through the Saio expansion in Kamurocho,\r\nTatsukawa and I kept the boy a secret."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "84||||4"
msgid "But that's when things went off the rails."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "85||||4"
msgid "You mean because Lo's eldest son ended up\r\ndead at the hands of Tsuneo Iwami?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86||||4"
msgid "Yeah. Exactly."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87||||4"
msgid "Jimmy's death meant Yuta was no longer just\r\ninsurance. He was the true heir to the triad."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88||||4"
msgid "That led the Saio to pry into Yuta's past\r\nin preparation for his eventual ascension."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89||||4"
msgid "At that point, it was only a matter of time\r\nuntil they figured out our fuck-up."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90||||4"
msgid "That's why Tatsukawa and I were\r\nso desperate to track Haruka down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91||||4"
msgid "We needed to find the baby and report it\r\nourselves before the triad found out."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92||||4"
msgid "It seemed like that was the only way\r\nwe'd be able to save ourselves."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94||||4"
msgid "Tatsukawa was the one who\r\neventually found Haruka and the child."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "95||||4"
msgid "Hirose-san had hidden them in a tiny rural\r\nvillage just a stone's throw away from here."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97||||4"
msgid "Soon as we had that, we reported it\r\nup, in detail, to the boss. His order?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98||||4"
msgid "Show no hesitation in eliminating the child."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99||||4"
msgid "Y'goddamn savages! What's yer damage!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "100||||4"
msgid "Y'were seriously gonna try n'\r\nmurder this little kid!? Huh!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "101||||4"
msgid "I didn't take Lo for being so hung up on\r\nsomething as meaningless as blood ties."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "102||||4"
msgid "It may seem inconsequential to you, but\r\nthings are different in the Saio Triad."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "103||||4"
msgid "To us, there is no higher law."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "104||||4"
msgid "Consider it a cultural difference."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "106||||4"
msgid "Anyway, once we pinned down the baby,\r\nall we had to do was wait for our chance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "107||||4"
msgid "We needed to lure Haruka away from\r\nHirose-san's watchful eye first, though."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "108||||4"
msgid "After all, would Yuta willingly become the\r\nSaio boss if he knew we'd killed his son?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "110||||4"
msgid "But, before we could carry out the plan,\r\nsomething unexpected happened."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "111||||4"
msgid "Even though Tatsukawa had been told\r\nby the boss to eliminate the child..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "112||||4"
msgid "...Instead he tried to betray us and sell\r\nthe baby to our enemy, Tsuneo Iwami."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "113||||4"
msgid "He figured, even if we followed orders,\r\nthe Saio might kill us for what we knew."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "114||||4"
msgid "That's why he turned to Tsuneo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "115||||4"
msgid "He brought Haruka to Kamurocho in secret\r\nso he could give the baby over to the Yomei."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "117||||4"
msgid "But just as she arrived, his plan crumbled."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "118||||4"
msgid "That day, Haruka was in a hit-and-run in\r\nKamurocho. The driver was Tatsukawa."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "119||||4"
msgid "T-Tatsukawa's the one who hit Haruka-chan!?\r\nWhy would he do that!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "120||||4"
msgid "If I had to guess, I'd say the accident\r\nwasn't the outcome he'd hoped for."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "121||||4"
msgid "Case in point, he didn't even take\r\nthe baby with him afterward."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "122||||4"
msgid "So you're saying Tatsukawa hit Haruka.\r\nAre you absolutely sure of that?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "123||||4"
msgid "Yeah, I am."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "124||||4"
msgid "And once all the dust settled, the baby\r\nwe had searched so tirelessly for..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "125||||4"
msgid "...Somehow had found its way right\r\ninto the arms of the Dragon of Dojima."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "126||||4"
msgid "Goddammit.\r\nI don't get any o' this shit..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "127||||4"
msgid "[Boss, we have the baby!\r\nLet's get out of here already!]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "128||||4"
msgid "Kiryu-san. This isn't exactly how\r\nI envisioned our reunion taking place."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "130||||4"
msgid "You'll have to excuse me for today."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "131||||4"
msgid "(Is Haruto okay? And what\r\nabout Yuta and the others?)"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "132||||4"
msgid "Yuta!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "133||||4"
msgid "A-Aniki."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "134||||4"
msgid "Where's Haruto?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "135||||4"
msgid "I had to let go of him on my way back."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "136||||4"
msgid "Cap's on the run with him now.\r\nI just hope he can shake those guys off."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "137||||4"
msgid "So you don't know where he is?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "138||||4"
msgid "No, but I'm sure he'll circle back\r\nt'the family office soon enough."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "140||||4"
msgid "Hey, Aniki..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "141||||4"
msgid "Aniki."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "143||||4"
msgid "Look, I know you're mad at me about\r\nwhat happened with Haruka-san."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "145||||4"
msgid "Oh, Aniki! I figured ya'd be here."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "146||||4"
msgid "Nagumo. Where is Haruto!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "147||||4"
msgid "Lemme apologize fer that!\r\nThose guys from before stole 'im from me..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "148||||4"
msgid "What the hell!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "149||||4"
msgid "N' after they took 'im,\r\nthey sped off in some kinda boat."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "150||||4"
msgid "A boat? We'll never catch them now!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "151||||4"
msgid "Y'can't jus' give up like that!\r\nDon't y'care about what happens t'yer kid!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "152||||4"
msgid "Of course I do! I jus' don't know\r\nhow to process all this, though."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "153||||4"
msgid "Not only is Haruto my son, but I'm\r\nalso the heir to a freakin' Chinese mafia?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "154||||4"
msgid "The words hardly make sense."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "156||||4"
msgid "Get it together, y'sad sack!\r\nIno's gettin' a boat ready fer us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "157||||4"
msgid "'Parently the fishermen're\r\ngonna pitch in on the search too."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "158||||4"
msgid "If nothin' else, we gotta come together\r\nn' do this fer Haruka-san."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "160||||4"
msgid "That includes you, Aniki.\r\nI'll show y'to Ino's boat."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "161||||4"
msgid "The boss n' the others're\r\nalready down there. C'mon!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "162||||4"
msgid "Right."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "163||||4"
msgid "Hey. The hell're y'doin', Yuta!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "164||||4"
msgid "Aniki. Ino said t'meet him by the dock."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "165||||4"
msgid "Dammit..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "167||||4"
msgid "What am I s'posed to do?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "168||||4"
msgid "This way, Aniki."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "169||||4"
msgid "Ino's waitin' over at the dock."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "170||||4"
msgid "Aniki. We need t'hurry."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "171||||4"
msgid "Let's get movin', Aniki."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "172||||4"
msgid "We're jus' about t'the boat, Aniki!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "173||||4"
msgid "Hey, this way!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "174||||4"
msgid "Everythin's ready fer ya!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "175||||4"
msgid "Jus' get on over here!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "176||||4"
msgid "Gotcha! Thanks, I really owe ya!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "177||||4"
msgid "Fisherman friend o' mine said\r\nhe saw a suspicious-lookin' ship!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "178||||4"
msgid "No doubt, the ones drivin' that\r\nship're the ones what took yer baby."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "179||||4"
msgid "Where're they headin'?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "180||||4"
msgid "Well y'know how they keep the cargo floatin'\r\non a separate island by the shipyard?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "181||||4"
msgid "'Parently they're tryin' t'hide there!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "182||||4"
msgid "A separate island for cargo?\r\nWhat do you mean?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "183||||4"
msgid "It'll make sense soon. Come t'think of it,\r\nthat'd be a great place t'store a boat."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "184||||4"
msgid "By the way, where's Masuzoe?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "185||||4"
msgid "He ran off when they started\r\nattackin' us at the shrine."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "186||||4"
msgid "Y'oughta jus' forget about him. We don't\r\ngotta protect that monster, boss."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "187||||4"
msgid "Don't be mean, Tagashira."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "188||||4"
msgid "I'm wonderin' who took Haruto t'begin\r\nwith, though. D'ya know, Aniki?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "189||||4"
msgid "It was the Jingweon Mafia."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "190||||4"
msgid "I'm certain of that.\r\nJoon-gi Han was there, too."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "191||||4"
msgid "They're in Hiroshima?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "192||||4"
msgid "Even so, I'm sure Tsuneo Iwami\r\nis the one givin' the orders."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "193||||4"
msgid "Patriarch. There's something\r\nI still can't quite wrap my head around."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "194||||4"
msgid "What is it?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "195||||4"
msgid "The connection between Onomichi\r\nand the Saio Triad."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "196||||4"
msgid "Hm?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "197||||4"
msgid "You said Yuta's been living in Onomichi\r\never since he was a small child."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "198||||4"
msgid "It seems like the <font_kind=yakuza_italic>heihaizi</font_kind> Masuzoe and\r\nTatsukawa had taken root here, too."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "199||||4"
msgid "There must be more to this\r\nthan you're choosing to let on."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "200||||4"
msgid "You're pretty sharp."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "201||||4"
msgid "Actually, the bond between the two\r\nruns deeper than you'd expect."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "202||||4"
msgid "Chairman Kurusu has been working with\r\nthe Saio Triad since before World War II."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "203||||4"
msgid "Before the war?\r\nThat's more'n 70 years ago!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "204||||4"
msgid "No shock there 'bout the chairman,\r\nbut I doubt Lo's that old."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "205||||4"
msgid "You're right. Lo's father was the one\r\nin charge of the Saio back then."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "206||||4"
msgid "They stopped talkin' after the war,\r\nbut negotiations picked back up 30 years ago."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "207||||4"
msgid "That's roughly about when\r\nthe Saio passed down to Lo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "208||||4"
msgid "30 years ago?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "209||||4"
msgid "And the thing that brought them back\r\ntogether? The <font_kind=yakuza_italic>heihaizi</font_kind> business."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "210||||4"
msgid "Hm?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "211||||4"
msgid "<font_kind=yakuza_italic>Heihaizi</font_kind> are basically Chinese children\r\nwho don't have any official documents."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "212||||4"
msgid "So, Lo was working to smuggle\r\nthose children into Onomichi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "213||||4"
msgid "It was all thanks to Chairman Kurusu\r\nthat he managed to pull it off."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "214||||4"
msgid "The chairman even helped forge\r\ndocuments for the smuggled <font_kind=yakuza_italic>heihaizi</font_kind>."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "215||||4"
msgid "With his help, almost 10,000 children\r\nhad new lives under the rising sun."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "216||||4"
msgid "Back in my heyday, I actually\r\nhelped out a bit with that."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "217||||4"
msgid "You did? Y'never told us anythin'."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "218||||4"
msgid "I still got all sorts of secrets\r\nI haven't clued you guys in on."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "219||||4"
msgid "Patriarch. What about\r\nChairman Kurusu's son, Tsuneo?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "220||||4"
msgid "Was he involved with the <font_kind=yakuza_italic>heihaizi</font_kind>, too?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "221||||4"
msgid "Hm? Yeah, I'm sure Tsuneo has\r\nhis own deal going with Lo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "222||||4"
msgid "I see. So that's the bond that ties\r\nOnomichi and the Saio Triad together."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "223||||4"
msgid "Hold on a sec. Ain't there somethin'\r\nelse tyin' the two together, Aniki?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "224||||4"
msgid "Hm?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "225||||4"
msgid "Remember? In Little Asia, Lo was talkin' about\r\nhow Onomichi had some kinda secret."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "226||||4"
msgid "[I doubt he knows the truth about Onomichi.]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "227||||4"
msgid "[The secret that town holds\r\ncan never be revealed.]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "228||||4"
msgid "A secret? Coulda fooled me."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "229||||4"
msgid "Well, uh... I think I may have an idea."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "230||||4"
msgid "Do ya now?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "231||||4"
msgid "I heard Chairman Kurusu's real influential\r\nwith all sortsa politician types."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "232||||4"
msgid "Not jus' local ones, either.\r\nI'm talkin' big-time government."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "233||||4"
msgid "They say he's even got ties t'that Fixer guy\r\nwho controls all o' Japan behind the scenes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "234||||4"
msgid "Maybe he has all those connections 'cause\r\no' some hidden power nobody knows about."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "235||||4"
msgid "Y'think that could be the secret of Onomichi?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "236||||4"
msgid "Wait, what the hell's all this 'bout a fixer?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "237||||4"
msgid "You mean Minoru Daidoji?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "238||||4"
msgid "Daidoji?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "239||||4"
msgid "Yeah, pretty sure that's his name.\r\nSurprised y'know it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "240||||4"
msgid "I heard it on TV or somethin'."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "241||||4"
msgid "Well, every single scandal after the war\r\nwound up gettin' pinned on him somehow."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "242||||4"
msgid "He's basically an old fart nobody likes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "243||||4"
msgid "But he's a government shadow, guys."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "244||||4"
msgid "They say the oil crisis n' the bubble collapse\r\nwere both conspiracies by the Fixer."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "245||||4"
msgid "Sounds like horse shit t'me. Y'been readin'\r\nthose damn tabloids again, huh?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "246||||4"
msgid "Hey, it's jus' over there!\r\nI can see it!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "247||||4"
msgid "Aniki. That cargo's what they use\r\nfer buildin' the ships."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "248||||4"
msgid "It's more convenient fer 'em t'keep the stuff\r\nout at sea instead o' in some dusty warehouse."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "249||||4"
msgid "So, that's where Haruto is."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "251||||4"
msgid "Sorry, Kiryu-san. Ino n' I are gonna\r\nstay and watch over the boat."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "252||||4"
msgid "Yeah, no problem."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "253||||4"
msgid "Oh, and I wanna apologize fer\r\nnot telling you about your girl."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "254||||4"
msgid "I just wasn't sure how to approach it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "255||||4"
msgid "But at the very least, I wanted to keep\r\nthe kid safe while I figured it out."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "256||||4"
msgid "Look how things ended up, though."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "258||||4"
msgid "Bring that baby back, Kiryu-san."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "259||||4"
msgid "By the way, yer girl told me\r\nsomething interesting."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "260||||4"
msgid "Apparently she wanted to go back to Okinawa\r\nonce she was confident she could raise the kid."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "261||||4"
msgid "Haruka said that?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "262||||4"
msgid "That's why she hadn't told you 'bout the kid."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "263||||4"
msgid "She wanted to be able to see you again\r\nwith her head held high. Y'know?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "264||||4"
msgid "Yeah."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "266||||4"
msgid "I promise... I'm going to do what it takes\r\nto bring Haruto back safe, Patriarch."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "267||||4"
msgid "(The number's blocked. Who could it be?)"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "268||||4"
msgid "You have my thanks for our fight earlier.\r\nI assure you the child is safe, Kiryu-san."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "269||||4"
msgid "You... Joon-gi Han!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "270||||4"
msgid "However, I must ask you to depart this island.\r\nYour presence here is quite unwelcome."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "272||||4"
msgid "On top of that, I have one more\r\nrather peculiar request to make of you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "273||||4"
msgid "If you comply, Haruto-kun will be returned\r\nto you without so much as a scratch."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "274||||4"
msgid "What do you want from us?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "275||||4"
msgid "Allow me to clarify: This is a task for Yuta-kun.\r\nPlease convey my message to him."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "276||||4"
msgid "I would like him to kill Big Lo of the Saio Triad."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "277||||4"
msgid "What the hell?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "278||||4"
msgid "Yuta-kun should be able to approach\r\nhis father in a way nobody else can."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "279||||4"
msgid "Case in point, we've been unable to even\r\n<font_kind=yakuza_italic>locate</font_kind> Lo, let alone get close to him."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "280||||4"
msgid "The paradigm shifted upon your\r\ninvasion into Little Asia, though."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "281||||4"
msgid "After all, that was the first time\r\nLo had shown himself in over two months."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "282||||4"
msgid "I think I understand now."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "283||||4"
msgid "You only took Haruto so\r\nyou could force Yuta to kill Lo!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "284||||4"
msgid "You have three days. If Yuta-kun succeeds,\r\nI doubt the Saio will let him live."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "285||||4"
msgid "However, if he is unable to complete my task..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "286||||4"
msgid "You'll kill Haruto?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "287||||4"
msgid "I can't believe that. You would really\r\nmurder a child who can't even walk yet?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "288||||4"
msgid "And all that talk of sportsmanship\r\nyou were so proud of before?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "289||||4"
msgid "Didn't you say you value elegance\r\nabove everything else!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "291||||4"
msgid "You should have come to me before\r\npulling a stunt like this, Joon-gi Han."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "292||||4"
msgid "Listen close. I'm coming to you, alone. No matter\r\nhow many of your men I have to go through."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "293||||4"
msgid "If it's a fight you want, it's a fight you'll get!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "295||||4"
msgid "Do you hear me!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "296||||4"
msgid "I understand."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "297||||4"
msgid "If you will indeed be coming by yourself,\r\nI wouldn't turn you away, Kiryu-san."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "298||||4"
msgid "Assuming you can make it to me, that is."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "299||||4"
msgid "I anticipate your arrival."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "300||||4"
msgid "What's going on, Kiryu-aniki?\r\nWhat did Joon-gi Han want from you?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "301||||4"
msgid "You already know the answer to that.\r\nFrom this point forward, I'll be going alone."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "302||||4"
msgid "Y'can't do that, Aniki! We got no idea\r\nhow many of 'em are waitin' fer ya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "303||||4"
msgid "Even yer gonna have trouble, Aniki."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "304||||4"
msgid "If we all went together, who knows\r\nwhat Han would do to Haruto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "305||||4"
msgid "This was the best deal I could make\r\nin the time I had. Sorry."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "307||||4"
msgid "As for Haruto, I promise I'll bring him back.\r\nJust you wait."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "308||||4"
msgid "Haruto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "309||||4"
msgid "You truly are a man of your word,\r\ncoming here all by yourself, Kiryu-san."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "310||||4"
msgid "I told you I would fight through\r\nwhatever you could throw at me."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "311||||4"
msgid "Alas, it would seem as though\r\nI am the only one left standing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "312||||4"
msgid "No matter how you slice it,\r\nthis is the end of the Jingweon Mafia."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "313||||4"
msgid "I have a question for you, though."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "314||||4"
msgid "The one who's been supporting your\r\nresurgence... It's Tsuneo Iwami, isn't it?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "315||||4"
msgid "Indeed. After the Little Asia fire,\r\nIwami approached us with a proposal."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "316||||4"
msgid "Our part was simply to fan the flames of\r\nwar between the Tojo Clan and the Saio."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "317||||4"
msgid "I see. And he'd give you enough money to\r\nbuy up half of Kamurocho, Stardust included."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "318||||4"
msgid "It was a rather generous offer. Only after\r\nwe had completed our task, of course."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "319||||4"
msgid "We were unfortunately unable to kill Big Lo,\r\nbut we did manage to take out his son, Jimmy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "320||||4"
msgid "What?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "321||||4"
msgid "That's right. We were working\r\nwith your friend Tatsukawa-kun as well."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "322||||4"
msgid "In fact, I was even present in Kamurocho\r\nwhen he struck Haruka Sawamura in his car."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "323||||4"
msgid "What!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "324||||4"
msgid "We were tasked with watching over Tatsukawa-kun\r\nto make sure he actually kidnapped the baby."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "325||||4"
msgid "Similar to our present situation, we hoped\r\nwe could force Yuta-kun to assassinate Lo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "326||||4"
msgid "Fine, but why did Tatsukawa hit Haruka!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "327||||4"
msgid "Simply put, that was a mistake.\r\nIt was an outcome nobody wanted."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "329||||4"
msgid "A few days before the accident, Tatsukawa-kun\r\nfound Haruka in the town where Hirose hid her."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "330||||4"
msgid "It must have been an extraordinary\r\nsurprise for her to see him there."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "331||||4"
msgid "But, he made quite a compelling\r\nargument to gain Haruka's trust."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "332||||4"
msgid "He claimed he would help her, even\r\nif it meant disobeying orders."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "333||||4"
msgid "Apparently that's the reason he gave for\r\nwanting to move her somewhere \"safer.\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "334||||4"
msgid "She must have thought it strange that he would\r\npass up such a clear opportunity to attack her."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "335||||4"
msgid "Beyond that, all he told her before he left\r\nwas to bring the child with her to Kamurocho."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "336||||4"
msgid "It makes sense that she would be suspicious\r\nof his reason for wanting her there."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "337||||4"
msgid "Tatsukawa... Why did he have\r\nto lure Haruka out to Kamurocho?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "338||||4"
msgid "The village she was hiding in was minuscule.\r\nEven a minor disturbance would be big news."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "339||||4"
msgid "If we wanted Yuta-kun to succeed\r\nin his assassination of Lo..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "340||||4"
msgid "...We had to ensure there was no chance\r\nthe Saio could find out we kidnapped the baby."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "342||||4"
msgid "To that end, Kamurocho was\r\nthe perfect place to carry out our plan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "343||||4"
msgid "Nobody in that pit would bat an eye\r\nat a girl screaming about her kidnapped son."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "345||||4"
msgid "But on that day..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "346||||4"
msgid "After they met up in an underground parking lot,\r\nTatsukawa-kun demanded Haruka get in his car."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "347||||4"
msgid "Had she agreed, she and Haruto would have\r\nbeen handed over to Iwami as planned."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "348||||4"
msgid "However, Haruka's well-placed mistrust of\r\nTatsukawa kept her from getting in the car."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "349||||4"
msgid "Then..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "350||||4"
msgid "Had her grip loosened even a little,\r\nwho knows what could have happened."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "351||||4"
msgid "Perhaps the child would have been\r\nsmeared across the pavement."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "352||||4"
msgid "However, she refused to let go\r\nof her son, at the cost of herself."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "353||||4"
msgid "The strength of a mother is truly incredible."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "354||||4"
msgid "I get it.\r\nYou bastards hurt Haruka."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "355||||4"
msgid "An unfortunate side effect."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "356||||4"
msgid "Regardless, we were simply following\r\nthe orders given to us by Tsuneo Iwami."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "357||||4"
msgid "Han. Are you telling me all of this now\r\nso my mind can be at peace when I kill you?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "358||||4"
msgid "Not at all. I told you because I'll no longer\r\nhave the chance once I reduce you to a corpse."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "359||||4"
msgid "And to die not knowing would be a shame."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "360||||4"
msgid "Now then, we can finally settle\r\nthis quarrel once and for all."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "361||||4"
msgid "Nobody can get in our way anymore."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "362||||4"
msgid "This time, we fight to the death, Kiryu-san!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "363||||4"
msgid "I hope so."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "364||||4"
msgid "This will be the Jingweon Mafia's\r\nfinal flourish!"
msgstr ""

